            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1628681795535-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine the<strong> panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> with the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>basil</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> basil crumb</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and a very generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
